message.content:
1. A woman sitting alone in a dimly lit room, holding her head in her hands, feeling foolish and desperate.
2. A man sitting in a noisy coffee shop, frowning and tapping his foot, feeling more irritated than peaceful.
3. A woman kneeling in a church, looking up at the ceiling, feeling troubled and lost.
4. A person sitting in a car, holding their head, feeling a dull headache building up.
5. A group of people celebrating in a fancy restaurant, feeling very successful.
6. A person sitting on a bench in a park, looking at the sky, feeling sorry about a failed relationship.
7. A person sitting in front of a blank paper, holding a pen, feeling miserable and unsure how to express their feelings.
8. A person lying in bed, staring at the ceiling, feeling distraught, worried, panicked, sick, scared, and sad.
9. A person sitting at a table, staring at an empty plate, feeling empty and unsatisfied.
10. A person standing in a crowded street, clenching their fists, feeling very angered.
11. A person typing on a computer, feeling the need to promote a TV series they love.
12. A person sitting on a couch, watching old movies, feeling melancholic.
13. A person holding their stomach, feeling like they are going to throw up after visiting a website.
14. A person waking up in bed, stretching, feeling a little brighter and eager to go outside.
15. A man and a woman walking on a bridge, smiling and feeling eternal hope.
16. A person holding their arm, feeling pain and bruising.
17. A person waking up in bed, rubbing their eyes, feeling groggy and tired.
18. A person sitting at a desk, tapping their fingers, feeling irritable.
19. A person sitting on a couch, staring at the wall, feeling emotional urges and trying to understand them.
20. A person sitting at a table, eating delicious food, feeling left out of a conversation.
21. A person walking in a village, looking at happy people, feeling appreciative of their happiness.
22. A person standing in front of a mirror, feeling humiliated, alone, and ugly.
23. A person walking in a park, trying to switch their negative thoughts, feeling distracted.
24. A person listening to a friend, feeling like they can tell what they are really feeling.
25. A person talking to a friend, feeling like they are loyal and will always be.
26. A person sitting in a restaurant, eating Chinese food, feeling not hostile towards anyone.
27. A person swinging a golf club, feeling like they are doing well.
28. A person sitting in a dark room, feeling like they are being punished for their past mistakes.
29. A person sitting in a meeting, feeling like they have to dumb themselves down to communicate effectively.
30. A person sitting in a room, feeling loyal to their conservative views.
31. A person sitting on a couch, feeling shaken by sudden news.
32. A person sitting in a chair, feeling funny and uncomfortable.
33. A person sitting on a bed, feeling troubled, stressed, down, and sick.
34. A person walking in a forest, feeling bad about killing but also exploring.
35. A person sitting in a room, feeling unsure and not optimistic about the future.
36. A person sitting on a bed, feeling bad about being depressed and wanting to starve.
37. A person standing in front of a mirror, feeling worthless.
38. A person singing a song, feeling too much but not caring.
39. A person sitting on a couch, feeling delicate and thoughtful.
40. A person sitting at a desk, feeling agitated and needing to leave work.
41. A person receiving a grade on a paper, feeling fearful and anxious.
42. A person walking in an airport, feeling jubilant and happy.
43. A person touching their hair, feeling lovely and silky.
44. A person talking about their fitness journey, feeling passionate and determined.
45. A person imagining holding someone, feeling warm and loving.
46. A person walking in a forest with their children, feeling like they have had a precious opportunity to get close to nature.
47. A person lying in bed, feeling sincere but troubled by their partner's character.
48. A person sitting in a classroom, feeling uncomfortable with high school.
49. A person sitting alone in a room, feeling heartbroken and alone.
50. A person sitting on a couch, feeling unsure and not content with their life.
